HEADWORD: Horntail
<hw>Horn"tail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of family (<fam>Urocerid⟦ae⟧</fam>) of large hymenopterous
insects, allied to the sawflies. The larv⟦ae⟧ bore in the wood of trees.
So called from the long, stout ovipositors of the females.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

